;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2852:\"<p>So with <a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2017/11/16/small-experiment-autoptimize-with-page-cache/\">that nice little page cache experiment</a> concluded, I started working on something that will definitively be included in the next version of Autoptimize; Extra Auto-optimizations!</p>\n<p>You can read all about it below or you can skip all of that and immediately <a href=\"https://github.com/futtta/ao_extra/archive/master.zip\">download the zipfile of the &#8220;AO Extra power-up&#8221;</a> from the <a href=\"https://github.com/futtta/ao_extra/\">Github repository</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ao_extra_screenshot.png\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-10567 aligncenter\" src=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ao_extra_screenshot-1024x585.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"625\" height=\"357\" srcset=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ao_extra_screenshot-1024x585.png 1024w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ao_extra_screenshot-300x171.png 300w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ao_extra_screenshot-624x356.png 624w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/ao_extra_screenshot.png 1166w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px\" /></a>The 3 features available now;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2015/10/19/no-emojis-were-speed-freakish/\">remove Emoji&#8217;s</a></li>\n<li>remove (version parameter from the) query string (not that big a deal, from a load time perspective, but still)</li>\n<li>the ability to have Autoptimize add the <code>async</code> attribute to the local or 3rd party JavaScript (local JS-files will be excluded automatically if added here).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There&#8217;s one extra feature that will very likely be added; optimize Google Fonts (because removing them is considered harsh, apparently).</p>\n<p>Do download, do test and do let me know if anything is broken in the comments or via <a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/contact/\">my contact form</a>. And If you have other ideas for extra features, do let me know too!</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2012/11/06/dipping-below-the-magical-1-second-page-load-time/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Dipping below the magical 1 second page load time\">Dipping below the magical 1 second page load time </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2013/04/01/easter-bunny-special-autoptimize-1-6-0/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Easter Bunny special: Autoptimize 1.6.0\">Easter Bunny special: Autoptimize 1.6.0 </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2014/09/30/amazed-by-autoptimize/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Amazed by Autoptimize take-up\">Amazed by Autoptimize take-up </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_autoptimize/~4/c8R3NQkEv2E\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2017/11/29/another-autoptimize-experiment-extras/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"16\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"